ponty vineyards, also known as vignobles ponty, is a wine estate of bordeaux wine in the canon fronsac appellation located on the right bank of the garonne river, 25 km away from bordeaux, close to the city of libourne. close to the pomerol and saint-emilion regions, canon fronsacâ€™s landscape of plateaus and hills snuggle into the confluence of two rivers: the isle and the dordogne. winemaking has been the family business for the ponty family for more than five generations. the vineyard currently produces five wines: chateau grand renouil, chateau du pavillon, petit renouil, clos virolle, and blanc de grand renouil.